The billionaire owner of the popular Tahir Guest Palace Hotel in Kano, Mr Tahir Fadallah, is dead. Senior special assistant to President Muhammadu Buhari on Media and Publicity, Malam Garba Shehu, confirmed Fadlallahâ€™s death via his Instagram page on Friday morning. He described the death of the hotelier as shocking and prayed to Allah to grant him Aljannatil Fiddaus and his family to bear the irreparable loss. LEADERSHIP learnt that Mr Fadlallah, who died in his native country, Lebanon, will be buried in Kano, Nigeria, where he lived for decades.